Nomura International plc Key Developments

Akamatsu Fund Appoints Nomura International plc as Additional Prime Broker
Jul 5 17
The Directors of the Akamatsu Fund announced that Nomura International plc has been appointed as a prime broker to the Fund pursuant to a Prime Brokerage Agreement between the Fund and Nomura dated 10th June 2016. Nomura has been appointed in addition to Credit Suisse Securities (Europe) Limited. The Investment Manager will determine based on the nature and type of transactions how the assets of the Fund will be allocated between the prime brokers. Nomura has also agreed to provide a custody service for all of the Fund's investments held on Nomura's books and records in its capacity as prime broker on the terms set out in the Prime Brokerage Agreement and in accordance with the rules of the FCA. Nomura will where possible segregate the Fund's securities from Nomura's proprietary assets in accordance with the terms of the Prime Brokerage Agreement.


Nomura International plc Presents at Mines and Money London 2016, Nov-28-2016
Oct 26 16
Nomura International plc Presents at Mines and Money London 2016, Nov-28-2016 . Venue: Islington Business Design Centre, 14-22 Coleman Fields, London N1 7AD, United Kingdom. Speakers: Timothy Ash, Head of EMEA Credit Strategy.


Nomura International plc Reports Audited Earnings Results for the Year Ended March 31, 2016
Aug 12 16
Nomura International plc reported audited earnings results for the year ended March 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported trading profit was $1,264,729,000 compared to $1,764,447,000 a year ago. Operating loss was $692,307,000 compared to $351,207,000 a year ago. Loss on ordinary activities before taxation was $749,176,000 compared to $451,677,000 a year ago. Loss for the financial year was $718,340,000 compared to $458,525,000 a year ago. Net cash flow from operating activities was $2,679,728,000 compared to $1,202,787,000 a year ago. Purchase of fixed assets was $71,278,000 compared to $64,339,000 a year ago.


